vpSysMibLevel.description: The level of the IBM VPN Policy MIB.

vpSysUpTime.name: vpSysUpTime
vpSysUpTime.description: The length of time in hundredths of a second that the policy definitions have been active.

vpSysCurTime.name: vpSysCurTime
vpSysCurTime.description: The current time in seconds since 1900.

vpSysHoursFromCut.name: vpSysHoursFromCut
vpSysHoursFromCut.description: The number of hours from Coordinated Universal Time which is abbreviated UTC as specified by the International Telecommunications Union. 1 = (UTC -0)...Coordinated Universal Time; United Kingdom 2 = (UTC -1)...Azores; Cape Verde 3 = (UTC -2)...Falkland Islands 4 = (UTC -3)...Greenland; East Brazil 5 = (UTC -4)...Central Brazil 6 = (UTC -5)...Eastern U.S.; Colombia 7 = (UTC -6)...Central U.S.; Honduras 8 = (UTC -7)...Mountain U.S. 9 = (UTC -8)...Pacific U.S.; Yukon 10 = (UTC -9)...Alaska 11 = (UTC-10)...Hawaii; Aleutian 12 = (UTC-11)...Bering Straits 13 = (UTC +1)...Norway; France 14 = (UTC +2)...Finland; South Africa 15 = (UTC +3)...Turkey; Saudi Arabia 16 = (UTC +4)...Gorki; Central Asia; Oman 17 = (UTC +5)...Pakistan 18 = (UTC +6)...Tashkent; Central Asia 19 = (UTC +7)...Thailand 20 = (UTC +8)...Western Australia 21 = (UTC +9)...Japan; Korea 22 = (UTC+10)...Eastern Australia 23 = (UTC+11)...Solomon Islands 24 = (UTC+12)...New Zealand

vpSysCurConfigSource.name: vpSysCurConfigSource
vpSysCurConfigSource.description: The current configuration source location(s). 1 = policy refresh in progress 2 = no policies were found in any source location 3 = policies were found in all source locations 4 = policies were found in SRAM 5 = policies were found in LDAP.

vpSysRefreshConfig.name: vpSysRefreshConfig
vpSysRefreshConfig.description: This object provides the ability to refresh the system's policies when set and provides the source of the last refresh when read. 1 = refresh policies from the operational (active) policy source location(s) 2 = refresh policies from the administrative (configured) policy source location(s).

vpLdapGblOperServerLdapLvl.name: vpLdapGblOperServerLdapLvl

vpLdapGblOperTimeOut.name: vpLdapGblOperTimeOut

vpLdapGblAdminLdapStatus.name: vpLdapGblAdminLdapStatus
vpLdapGblAdminLdapStatus.description: The configured status of the LDAP Administrative parameter values.

vpLdapGblAdminPolicyBaseName.name: vpLdapGblAdminPolicyBaseName
vpLdapGblAdminPolicyBaseName.description: The configured Base Name to use when retrieving policies from the LDAP Server.

vpLdapGblAdminPortNumber.name: vpLdapGblAdminPortNumber
vpLdapGblAdminPortNumber.description: The configured Port Number to use when retrieving policies from the LDAP Server.

vpLdapGblAdminTimeOut.name: vpLdapGblAdminTimeOut
vpLdapGblAdminTimeOut.description: The configured Time-Out period in seconds to use when retrieving policies from the LDAP Server.

vpLdapGblAdminRetryInterval.name: vpLdapGblAdminRetryInterval
vpLdapGblAdminRetryInterval.description: The configured Retry Interval in seconds to use when retrieving policies from the LDAP Server.

vpLdapGblAdminUserId.name: vpLdapGblAdminUserId
vpLdapGblAdminUserId.description: The configured User ID to use when retrieving policies from the LDAP Server.

vpPolIpsecManualTunId.description: The ID of manually configured IPSec Phase-2 Tunnel.

vpPolicyRulePriEntry.description: A VPN Policy Rule Priority Table entry.

vpPolRulePriTrafficProfileRef.description: The name of the Traffic Profile for the VPN Policy Rule. This name can be used to index directly into the vpTrafficProfileTable.

vpPolRulePriValidityPeriodRef.description: The name of the Validity Period for the VPN Policy. This name can be used to index directly into the vpValidityPeriodTable.

vpPolRulePriRsvpActionRef.description: The name of the RSVP Action for the VPN Policy. This name can be used to index directly into the vpRsvpActionTable.

vpPolRulePriDiffServActionRef.name: vpPolRulePriDiffServActionRef
vpPolRulePriDiffServActionRef.description: The name of the Differential Services Action for the VPN Policy. This name can be used to index directly into the vpDiffServActionTable.

vpPolRulePriIsakmpActionRef.name: vpPolRulePriIsakmpActionRef
vpPolRulePriIsakmpActionRef.description: The name of the ISAKMP Action for the VPN Policy. This name can be used to index directly into the vpIsakmpActionTable.

vpPolRulePriSecurityActionRef.name: vpPolRulePriSecurityActionRef
vpPolRulePriSecurityActionRef.description: The name of the Security Action for the VPN Policy. This name can be used to index directly into the vpSecurityActionTable.

vpPolRulePriIpsecManualTunId.name: vpPolRulePriIpsecManualTunId
vpPolRulePriIpsecManualTunId.description: The ID of manually configured IPSec Phase-2 Tunnel.

vpPolicyCorTable.description: The VPN Policy Correlation Table. This table can be used to correlate VPN Policies with VPN Policy Rules. A VPN Policy may be associated with one or more VPN Policy Rules.

vpPolicyCorEntry.name: vpPolicyCorEntry
vpPolicyCorEntry.description: A VPN Policy Correlation Table entry.

vpPolCorRuleOrder.description: The order of this VPN Rule relative to other VPN Rules for this VPN Policy.

vpPolCorRulePriOrder.name: vpPolCorRulePriOrder
vpPolCorRulePriOrder.description: The priority of this VPN Rule relative to all VPN Rules. This number can be used to index directly into the vpPolicyRulePriTable.

vpTrafProfName.description: The name of the Traffic Profile.

vpTrafProfHiProtocol.description: The high protocol number for this Traffic Profile.

vpTrafProfLoProtocol.name: vpTrafProfLoProtocol
vpTrafProfLoProtocol.description: The low protocol number for this Traffic Profile.

vpTrafProfSrcHiAddr.name: vpTrafProfSrcHiAddr
vpTrafProfSrcHiAddr.description: The high source IP Address for this Traffic Profile.

vpTrafProfSrcLoAddr.name: vpTrafProfSrcLoAddr
vpTrafProfSrcLoAddr.description: The low source IP Address for this Traffic Profile.

vpTrafProfSrcHiPort.description: The high source port number for this Traffic Profile.

vpTrafProfSrcLoPort.description: The low source port number for this Traffic Profile.

vpTrafProfDstHiAddr.name: vpTrafProfDstHiAddr
vpTrafProfDstHiAddr.description: The high destination IP Address for this Traffic Profile.

vpTrafProfDstLoAddr.name: vpTrafProfDstLoAddr
vpTrafProfDstLoAddr.description: The low destination IP Address for this Traffic Profile.

vpTrafProfDstLoPort.name: vpTrafProfDstLoPort
vpTrafProfDstLoPort.description: The low destination port number for this Traffic Profile.

vpTrafProfRcvTosByteMask.name: vpTrafProfRcvTosByteMask
vpTrafProfRcvTosByteMask.description: The Type of Service (TOS) Byte Mask Value. This is a 8-bit mask which is be applied to an incoming packet's TOS byte.

vpTrafProfRcvTosByteMatch.name: vpTrafProfRcvTosByteMatch
vpTrafProfRcvTosByteMatch.description: The Type of Service (TOS) Byte Match Value. This is a 8-bit pattern which is used to compare to the value of the result of the ANDing of the incoming TOS byte and the mask value.

vpTrafProfLocIdType.name: vpTrafProfLocIdType
vpTrafProfLocIdType.description: The Traffic Local Identification Type. This value is used in interpreting the Traffic Local Identification Value. 1 = IP V4 Address 2 = Fully Qualified Domain Name 3 = User Fully Qualified Domain Name 9 = Domain Name 10 = Global Name 11 = Key ID 99 = Any

vpTrafProfLocIdValue.name: vpTrafProfLocIdValue
vpTrafProfLocIdValue.description: The Traffic Local Identification Value. See vpTrafProfLocIdType for more information.

vpTrafIfInAddr.name: vpTrafIfInAddr
vpTrafIfInAddr.description: The Traffic Interface Inbound IP Address.

vpTrafIfOutAddr.name: vpTrafIfOutAddr
vpTrafIfOutAddr.description: The Traffic Interface Outbound IP Address.

vpTrafficRemIdEntry.name: vpTrafficRemIdEntry
vpTrafficRemIdEntry.description: A Traffic Remote Identification Table entry.

vpTrafRemIdType.name: vpTrafRemIdType
vpTrafRemIdType.description: The Traffic Remote Identification Type. This value is used in interpreting the Traffic Remote Identification Value. 1 = IP V4 Address 2 = Fully Qualified Domain Name 3 = User Fully Qualified Domain Name 9 = Domain Name 10 = Global Name 11 = Key ID

vpTrafRemIdValue.name: vpTrafRemIdValue
vpTrafRemIdValue.description: The Traffic Remote Identification Value. See vpTrafRemIdValueType for more information.

vpTrafRemIdAuthMode.name: vpTrafRemIdAuthMode
vpTrafRemIdAuthMode.description: The Traffic Remote Identification Authentication Mode. 1 = preshared key 2 = certificate

vpValPrdName.name: vpValPrdName
vpValPrdName.description: The name of the Validity Period.

vpValPrdStartTime.name: vpValPrdStartTime
vpValPrdStartTime.description: The Validity Start Time in seconds since 1900. A value of xFF:FF:FF:FF signifies forever.

vpValPrdEndTime.name: vpValPrdEndTime
vpValPrdEndTime.description: The Validity End Time in seconds since 1900. A value of xFF:FF:FF:FF signifies forever.

vpValPrdMonthMask.name: vpValPrdMonthMask
vpValPrdMonthMask.description: The Month Mask for this Validity Period. Each Bit in the Mask represents a month. Octet 2 Octet 1 ---------------------- ------------------------------- 7-4 3 2 1 0 7 6 5 4 3 2 1 0 0's Jan Feb Mar Apr May Jun Jul Aug Sep Oct Nov Dec

vpValPrdDaysMask.name: vpValPrdDaysMask
vpValPrdDaysMask.description: The Days-Of-The-Week Mask for this Validity Period. Each Bit in the Mask represents a day. Octet 1 ------------------------------- 7 6 5 4 3 2 1 0 0 Mon Tue Wed Thr Fri Sat Sun

vpValPrdStartTod.name: vpValPrdStartTod
vpValPrdStartTod.description: The Validity Period Start Time-Of-Day. It is represented in the number of seconds since 00:00 AM. A value of xFF:FF:FF:FF signifies all day.

vpValPrdStopTod.name: vpValPrdStopTod
vpValPrdStopTod.description: The Validity Period End Time-Of-Day. It is represented in the number of seconds since 00:00 AM. A value of xFF:FF:FF:FF signifies all day.

vpRsvpActName.name: vpRsvpActName
vpRsvpActName.description: The name of the RSVP Action.

vpRsvpActPermission.name: vpRsvpActPermission
vpRsvpActPermission.description: Permit or deny RSVP requests of with the type of vpRsvpActFlowSvrType.

vpRsvpActMaxRatePerFlow.name: vpRsvpActMaxRatePerFlow
vpRsvpActMaxRatePerFlow.description: The Maximum Amount of Bandwidth in Kbytes-Per-Second that RSVP should be allowed to allocate for one individual flow.

vpRsvpActMaxTokenBucketPerFlow.name: vpRsvpActMaxTokenBucketPerFlow
vpRsvpActMaxTokenBucketPerFlow.description: The Maximum Token Bucket to allocate for a RSVP flow.

vpRsvpActMaxFlowDuration.name: vpRsvpActMaxFlowDuration
vpRsvpActMaxFlowDuration.description: The Maximum Amount of Time in seconds that RSVP should allow a reservation to be active.

vpRsvpActMinDelay.name: vpRsvpActMinDelay
vpRsvpActMinDelay.description: The Minimum Delay in milliseconds that RSVP should be allowed to reserve for an individual RSVP reservation.

vpRsvpActDiffSvrRef.name: vpRsvpActDiffSvrRef
vpRsvpActDiffSvrRef.description: The name of the Differential Services Action for this RSVP Action. This name can be used to index directly into the vpDiffServActionTable.

vpRsvpActMatches.name: vpRsvpActMatches
vpRsvpActMatches.description: The number of packet matches for this RSVP Action.

vpDiffServActionEntry.name: vpDiffServActionEntry
vpDiffServActionEntry.description: A Differential Services Action Table entry.

vpDifSrvActName.name: vpDifSrvActName
vpDifSrvActName.description: The name of the Differential Services Action.

vpDifSrvActPermission.name: vpDifSrvActPermission
vpDifSrvActPermission.description: Permit or Deny traffic matching the Traffic Profile. This parameter is used as a filter rule to control which IP traffic is allowed to be forwarded.

vpDifSrvActQuePriority.name: vpDifSrvActQuePriority
vpDifSrvActQuePriority.description: The Queue Priority to be used for traffic.

vpDifSrvActBwType.name: vpDifSrvActBwType
vpDifSrvActBwType.description: Specifies whether the bandwidth share is a percentage of the output bandwidth or an absolute number in Kbytes-Per-Second. See also vpDifSrvActBwShare.

vpDifSrvActBwShare.name: vpDifSrvActBwShare
vpDifSrvActBwShare.description: The amount of bandwidth to allocate for packets matching this Differential Services Action. Bandwidth may be specified by percentage of output bandwidth or by an absolute number in Kbytes-Per-Second. See also vpDifSrvActBwType.

vpDifSrvActTransTosByteMask.name: vpDifSrvActTransTosByteMask
vpDifSrvActTransTosByteMask.description: The Type of Service (TOS) Byte Mask Value. This is a 8-bit mask which is be applied to an incoming packet's TOS byte.

vpDifSrvActTransTosByteMatch.name: vpDifSrvActTransTosByteMatch
vpDifSrvActTransTosByteMatch.description: The Type of Service (TOS) Byte Match Value. This is a 8-bit pattern which is used to compare to the value of the result of the ANDing of the incoming TOS byte and the mask value.

vpDifSrvActMatches.name: vpDifSrvActMatches
vpDifSrvActMatches.description: The number of packet matches for this Differential Services Action.

vpIkActName.name: vpIkActName
vpIkActName.description: The name of the ISAKMP Action.

vpIkActExchangeMode.name: vpIkActExchangeMode
vpIkActExchangeMode.description: The Exchange Mode for ISAKMP Phase-1 negotiations.

vpIkActConnSaLifeTime.name: vpIkActConnSaLifeTime
vpIkActConnSaLifeTime.description: The Lifetime of the ISAKMP Phase-1 Connection. This specifies the amount of time in seconds after which the Phase-1 Security Association is renegotiated.

vpIkActConnSaLifeSize.name: vpIkActConnSaLifeSize
vpIkActConnSaLifeSize.description: The Lifesize of the ISAKMP Phase-1 Connection. This specifies the amount of traffic in Kbytes after which the Phase-1 Security Association is renegotiated.

vpIkActPolicyRole.name: vpIkActPolicyRole
vpIkActPolicyRole.description: The ISAKMP Policy Role. 1 = Initiator 2 = Responder 3 = Initiator and Responder

vpIkActMinPercentRefresh.name: vpIkActMinPercentRefresh
vpIkActMinPercentRefresh.description: The minimium percentage of the ISAKMP Phase-1 proposals Lifetime that should be considered valid during ISAKMP Phase-1 negotiations.

vpIkActAutoStart.name: vpIkActAutoStart
vpIkActAutoStart.description: The ISAKMP Auto Start setting. When enabled the Security Association must be automatically negotiated at system initialization.

vpIkActMatches.name: vpIkActMatches
vpIkActMatches.description: The number of packet matches for this ISAKMP Action.

vpIkPropName.name: vpIkPropName
vpIkPropName.description: The name of the ISAKMP Proposal.

vpIkPropAuthMethod.name: vpIkPropAuthMethod
vpIkPropAuthMethod.description: The Authentication Method to use in ISAKMP Phase-1 negotiations.

vpIkPropHashAlgo.name: vpIkPropHashAlgo
vpIkPropHashAlgo.description: The Hash Algorithm to use in ISAKMP Phase-1 negotiations.

vpIkPropCipherAlgo.name: vpIkPropCipherAlgo
vpIkPropCipherAlgo.description: The Cipher Algorithm to use in ISAKMP Phase-1 negotiations.

vpIkPropDiffHellmanGrpId.name: vpIkPropDiffHellmanGrpId
vpIkPropDiffHellmanGrpId.description: The Diffie Hellman Group to use in ISAKMP Phase-1 negotiations.

vpIkPropSaLifeTime.name: vpIkPropSaLifeTime
vpIkPropSaLifeTime.description: The Lifetime of the ISAKMP Phase-1 Connection. This specifies the amount of time in seconds after which the Phase-1 Security Association is renegotiated.

vpIkPropSaLifeSize.name: vpIkPropSaLifeSize
vpIkPropSaLifeSize.description: The Lifesize of the ISAKMP Phase-1 Connection. This specifies the amount of traffic in Kbytes after which the Phase-1 Security Association is renegotiated.

vpIsakmpCorTable.name: vpIsakmpCorTable
vpIsakmpCorTable.description: The ISAKMP Correlation Table. This table can be used to to correlate ISAKMP Actions with ISAKMP Proposals. An ISAKMP Action may be associated with one or more ISAKMP Proposals.

vpIkCorPropOrder.name: vpIkCorPropOrder
vpIkCorPropOrder.description: The Proposal Order for the ISAKMP Action.

vpIkCorPropName.name: vpIkCorPropName
vpIkCorPropName.description: The name of the ISAKMP Proposal. This name can be used to index directly into the vpIsakmpProposalTable.

vpIsakmpActiveInstEntry.name: vpIsakmpActiveInstEntry
vpIsakmpActiveInstEntry.description: An ISAKMP Active Instance Table entry.

vpIkActInstOrder.name: vpIkActInstOrder
vpIkActInstOrder.description: The Active Instance Creation Order for the ISAKMP Action.

vpIkActInstTunnelIndex.name: vpIkActInstTunnelIndex
vpIkActInstTunnelIndex.description: The ISAKMP Phase-1 Tunnel Index (ikeTunnelIndex from the IBM IPSec MIB).

vpSecActName.name: vpSecActName
vpSecActName.description: The name of the Security Action.

vpSecActType.name: vpSecActType
vpSecActType.description: The Type of action which should be performed to packets matching the Traffic Profile of a Policy specifying this action.

vpSecActTunStartAddr.name: vpSecActTunStartAddr
vpSecActTunStartAddr.description: The IP Address of the IPSec Tunnel Starting Point.

vpSecActTunEndAddr.name: vpSecActTunEndAddr
vpSecActTunEndAddr.description: The IP Address of the IPSec Tunnel Ending Point.

vpSecActLocProxyType.name: vpSecActLocProxyType
vpSecActLocProxyType.description: The Local Proxy Type. This value is used in interpreting the Local Proxy Value. 1 = IP V4 Address 2 = Fully Qualified Domain Name 3 = User Fully Qualified Domain Name 4 = IP V4 Address Subnet 7 = IP V4 Address Range 9 = Domain Name 10 = Global Name 11 = Key ID

vpSecActLocProxyValue.name: vpSecActLocProxyValue
vpSecActLocProxyValue.description: The Local Proxy Value. See vpSecActLocProxyType for more information.

vpSecActRemProxyType.name: vpSecActRemProxyType
vpSecActRemProxyType.description: The Remote Proxy Type. This value is used in interpreting the Remote Proxy Value. 1 = IP V4 Address 2 = Fully Qualified Domain Name 3 = User Fully Qualified Domain Name 4 = IP V4 Address Subnet 7 = IP V4 Address Range 9 = Domain Name 10 = Global Name 11 = Key ID

vpSecActRemProxyValue.name: vpSecActRemProxyValue
vpSecActRemProxyValue.description: The Remote Proxy Value. See vpSecActRemProxyType for more information.

vpSecActSaRefreshThresh.name: vpSecActSaRefreshThresh
vpSecActSaRefreshThresh.description: The IPSec Security Association Refresh Threshold. The value is represented as a percentage of the Security Association Lifetime or Security Association Lifesize.

vpSecActMinPercentRefresh.name: vpSecActMinPercentRefresh
vpSecActMinPercentRefresh.description: The minimium percentage of the Security Associations Lifetime that should be considered valid during IPSec negotiations.

vpSecActTunnelInTunnel.name: vpSecActTunnelInTunnel
vpSecActTunnelInTunnel.description: Specifies whether or not this IPSec Tunnel is protected by another tunnel.

vpSecActAutoStart.name: vpSecActAutoStart
vpSecActAutoStart.description: The IPSec Auto Start setting. When enabled the Security Association must be automatically negotiated at system initialization.

vpSecActDontFragBitHandling.name: vpSecActDontFragBitHandling
vpSecActDontFragBitHandling.description: The IPSec processing to perform on the Don't Fragment (DF) Bit when building a new package header. in the original 1 = Copy the DF Bit from the orginal header to the new header 2 = Set (Turn On) the DF Bit in the new header 3 = Clear (Turn Off) the DF Bit in the new header

vpSecActMatches.name: vpSecActMatches
vpSecActMatches.description: The number of packet matches for this Securtiy Action.

vpSecPropName.description: The name of the Security Proposal.

vpSecurityEspTransEntry.name: vpSecurityEspTransEntry
vpSecurityEspTransEntry.description: A Security ESP Transform Table entry.

vpSecEspTransName.description: The name of the ESP Transform.

vpSecEspTransSaLifeSize.name: vpSecEspTransSaLifeSize
vpSecEspTransSaLifeSize.description: The Lifesize of the ESP Security Association. This specifies the amount of traffic in Kbytes after which the ESP Security Association is renegotiated.

vpSecurityIpcompTransEntry.name: vpSecurityIpcompTransEntry

vpSecCorPropRef.name: vpSecCorPropRef
